msgid ""
"Generally Primes are preferred over zooms in video. (Some people, prefer"
" it over zooms as well for photography — but this is a matter of taste"
" and of how you work.) Why is that? A psychological reason is that eyes"
" cannot zoom either, so zooming is hardly ever used in video. The"
" technical reason is that Primes are cheaper to build whilst offering"
" better quality: Better sharpness, bigger aperture (for limiting the"
" :abbr:`DOF (Depth of Field)`). Opening the aperture gives you a very"
" nice look."
msgstr ""

