#: ../../tips_and_tricks/shooting_tips/shooting_with_your_DSLR.rst:113
msgid ""
"The White Balance should be set as accurate as possible because DSLRs"
" only support 8 bit per color channel (see also the chapter about the"
" :doc:`Waveform Monitor </tips_and_tricks/scopes/waveform_and_rgb_parade"
">`). If done wrong, much of the color information is lost."
msgstr ""

#: ../../tips_and_tricks/shooting_tips/shooting_with_your_DSLR.rst:115
msgid ""
"DSLRs also offer different camera profiles with different contrast,"
" saturation and other settings. Usually low saturation is preferred over"
" high saturation — especially because raising the saturation can be done"
" in post, and because high in-camera saturation settings can lead to"
" color clipping."
msgstr ""

